<p>December 5, 1996</p>


<p align="center"><b>URGENT - URGENT - URGENT</b></p>



<p>Artie Zuschauerdienst<BR>

2A, rue de la Fonderie<BR>

F-67080 Strasbourg Cedex</p>


<p><i>Attn: Martin Meissonnier, Christoph Jorg, ARTE Thema</i></p>


<p>Dear Sirs,</p>

<p>On the 19th November this year your Thema television program
ran a segment on the electromagnetic Bomb paper which we
sponsored to the InfoWarCon 5conference. We understand that some
of the coverage may not have been entirely accurate.</p>


<p>We would be most interested in ARTE-Thema providing our
principal, Mr Winn Schwartau, an internationally recognized
authority on the subject of Information Warfare and
Cyber-Terrorism, with the opportunity to elaborate on the context
and the importance of this paper in a television interview. Winn
is happy to answer any questions which you think may be of
interest to your audience.</p>


<p>We remind you that the paper in question is covered by
copyright, and ARTE-Thema published this material without the
prior consent of infowar.com or the author of the paper. Your
internet posting (~/thema/19961119/liens.html) also does not
mention our primary site, www infowar.com, which has posted the
paper since early October.</p>


<p>Therefore, we believe that ARTE-Thema should provide us with
the right of reply on this topic. The topic is one of major
importance and we believe that it should receive proper coverage.
We are sure that your viewers will appreciate the whole story
behind the paper.</p>


<p>Mr Schwartau will be in Sweden between dates from December 7
to December 13, 1996. Please contact me at betty@infowar.com or
813-367-7277. Perhaps you will be interested in capturing this
opportunity. I am sure a videoconference interview can be easily
arranged from your end. </p>


<p>We thank you for your cooperation in this matter.</p>


<p>Best Regards,<BR>

Betty G. O'Hearn<BR>

Assistant to Mr. Winn Schwartau</p>

<BR>


