<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>

Memorandum on 'Arab Intranet' to be signed next week.<BR>

</h3>
</center>

<BR>
                   By a staff reporter<BR>

 <P>                   A MEMORANDUM of Understanding for the establishment of
an Arab Intranet will be
                    signed in Dubai next week during a seminar organised by
the Ajman University College of
                    Science and Technology (AUCST).

<P>                    Announcing this at a Press conference yesterday, the
chairman of AUCST and president
                    of Private Arabian Institution League of Higher
Education (PAILHE), Dr Saeed Salman,
                    said that the establishment of the Arab Intranet is a
protective strategy against the
                    invasion of Internet information.

  <P>                  "The Arab Intranet will be an accurate information
resource to protect our society and
                    correct the misleading information about the Arab
countries on the Internet."

  <P>                  He said that the two-day symposium to be held from
October 20 at the Dubai Chamber of
                    Commerce and Industry, would be attended by many
European and Arab universities.

   <P>                 The symposium, entitled 'Unitwin Universities within an
Arab Intranet' (Intranet is the
                    local network area from the main international
network), will discuss several topics such
                    as investing information resources using information
technology, strategies on
                    information technology in education and training,
network technology for teaching
                    international commerce and the future challenge of
maximising the utilisation of
                    information technology while maintaining the Arab culture.

    <P>                Other work papers will cover the role of the Arab
League in information resources,
                    private imminent institution networking strategies, the
integration of regional
                    governmental and private universities networks and the
information technology for
                    re-engineering in trading process.

          <P>         Dr Salman believed that the Arab Intranet would serve
the educational process in the
                    Arab countries.

    <P>                The idea of establishing the Arab Intranet was
originated by the AUCST based on the fact
                    that some private and government Arab universities have
the information technology
                    while others have the information.

        <P>            "In the future all Arab universities can join the
Intranet. This will serve education in the
                    first place," Dr Salman said.

          <P>          He said that the establishment of the Arab Intranet
would not be difficult because its base
                    already exists. He said the Intranet would be
supervised by the Arab League but would
                    have a separate board of trustees.

             <P>      The details on the financing and membership of the net
will be discussed at a meeting in  Cairo later, Dr Salman said.<BR>



</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br>
