<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/class1.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>

You can hide yourself, but it takes time and effort, and sometimes you walk a fine line. <BR>

</h3>
</center>
 </table>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>1. Avoid first tier ID by having utilities, phone bills, etc.
in another name, or company name.  Sometimes you can get
an anonymous account, if you post funds in advance.

<LI>2. Get confidentiality on your driver's license and voter's
records.  We have it here in CA, I don't know about elsewhere.

<LI>3. Get a PO Box.  Don't associate your home address with the 
PO Box.

<LI>4. Never, never get mail at home.  Anything that comes in your
name, mark "wrong address" and send it back unopened.

<LI>5. Build credit using your PO Box-- can be done.  

<LI>6. Refuse to provide your SSN whenever possible.  Be prepared with
an alternative 9 digit number, but be sure you let people know
it's not an SSN, it's your alternative number.

<LI>7. Make 800, 888 calls from other phones, use a pre-paid card,
or use your cell phone.  Caller ID blocking doesn't work on
800, 888, or sometimes other long-distance numbers.  Your
long distance carrier will give you away.
</UL>
<BR>
Good luck,<BR>

EN<BR>



</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
