<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h2>
Spam lists.
</h2>
</center>
 
<BR>

<P>You might be interested to know about a list that appears to be gaining in
credibility among Internet marketers, the DEMA (Direct Email marketing
Association) list.  I detest unsolicted commercial email but joined the list
just to keep tabs on what they're up to.

<P>Topics include such things as which newsgroup email-gathering software is
the best, how to make your unsolicted email targeted for the group so it's
more easily accepted, etc.

<P>I was mildly amused once that the moderator clipped a poster's sig file
because it exceeded the "6 lines dictated by netiquette"!  I emailed and
asked, "Is it ok to waste someone else's resources but not your own?".  He
wasn't amused, though.  Needless to say my comments didn't make it to the list.

DEMA postings are archived at <a href="http://kww.com/dema/">http://kww.com/dema/</a>.

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br>
<IMG ALT="[Bomb2]" SRC="../../images/bomb2_li.gif" width=580><p>
