<tr>
<td width=440>


<H2>
Hackers Open Letter</H2>
<BR>
        <P>this is an open letter to the internet community</P>
 
        <p>this will dispel many rumors about why a paticular mail bombing
        occured in recent months.  i will not discuss each one that we
        bombed but i will discuss some of them.</p>
 
        <p>this letter is dedicated to PED who couldn't even get a
        simple article on mail bombs right in TIME magazine.
        we did not spam anyone.  we used a listserv/majordomo
        attack to MAILBOMB.  yes, there is a difference.</P>
   
       <p> the media labeled us long ago whether they know it or not
        and they will continue to do so.  we are hackers and phreaks
        and we have no long term agenda.  we do what we want when we want
        and at other people's expense. if we go down for any of our
        crimes so be it.  that is part of the path we choose and
        no one will stop us.</P>
      
        <P>why a listserv/majordomo attack?  there are several subtle
        advantages to this kind of mailbomb.  the first being
        that all mail does not come from us.  yes, we know you can
        track it back to the account we used but that does you
        nothing.  since some of the mailing lists are gated to
        bitnet and some are manually done, even after the first
        wave of unsubscribes, the victim will continue to get
        mail.</P>

        <P> the net is chaos</P>
        <P>we are on the net</P>
        <P>therefore we must be chaotic</P>

         <P>why this letter?  because no one can figure out why some
        of the people were bombed.  it should be more than clear
        but i didn't realize how out of touch "technology" 
        journalists, publishers, and other media goons really are.</P>
   
        <P>why our actions in general?  too many people on the net do not
        belong.  we remember the net back when there were only one
        thousand people on irc.  we remember the net back when there
        were hundreds of newsgroups.  we remember when we could connect
        to any site at any time and have no trouble transferring one
        or two files quickly.  too many companies are intent upon
        destroying the net and worrying only about their stuffed
        pockets.  we are just one group helping to reclaim what
        used to be.</P>
   
        <P>the net may not belong to us but we can safely say it is more
        ours than the capitalist pigs that are infesting it 
        now.  clueless yuppies are the other 'entity' that are 
        bringing the net to its knees.  if you do not know how to use 
        the net, stay off of it.  like others, we are losing control 
        of the net and want to take a last stab at revenge.  revenge 
        may be childish and immature but it is damn fun and very rewarding.</P>
  
 
        <P>on to the bombs...</P>
     
        <P>70277.2502@compuserve.com     rush limbaugh</P>
        <P>we do not believe much needs to be said here but since it took
        a call from rush to ped to inform a senior technology editor
        we can only assume it was not as clear.  fat political hag.
        this bomb had nothing to do with the cda.</P>
       
        <P>71511.460@compuserve.com      ross perot</P>
        <P>all those millions of dollars and you can not get an ear job?
        quit trying to buy the masses.  if you really care about
        this country, put your money back into it without being
        a president.</P>

        <P>corpcomm@aol.com              america online corporate communications</P>
        <P>insulting advertising on television.  aol is also the first
        to successfully complete a snail mail spam with their shitty
        disks.</P>
     
        <P>sermoner1@aol.com             aol staff in charge of scientology area</P>
        <P>the cult of scientology should be eradicated.  the law should
        step in and force them out of business since they are not a church.
        the continual abuse of non-believers and harassment of those who
