<H4>11/19/96</H4>
 
<LI>The Joint Chiefs of Staff <a href="../mil_c4i/joint/joint.html-ssi">Report on Information Warfare</a> Now Available. The Second Edition of "Information Warfare: Legal, Regulatory, Policy and Organizational Considerations for Assurance" This invaluable report offers a well-balanced analysis of the DoD's concerns about information security and electronic national security.   Thank you to Major Steven J. Spano, and the support  from the Joint Chiefs of Staff, J6K, Information Warfare Division for making this possible.  This report is downloadable,  3.12 Meg in Word  format. <BR>

<BR>
<LI>The Militarily Critical Technologies List<BR>What Is the MCTL Process?  It is the systemic ongoing assessment and analyses of technologies to determine which technologies are <U>Militarily Critical</U>. 
Infowar.com has been given permission to publish the <a href="../mil_c4i/mctl/mctl.html-ssi">Military Critical Technologies List - Part I:  Weapons Systems Technologies</a>.  It is available in .pdf format.   This is the first of three parts.  Part two:  Weapons of Mass Production and  Part three: Critical Developing Technologies are in development and will be published when completed and made available to us. <BR><BR>

<LI>Are We Living in a state of National Emergency? According to Executive 
Order #12923 we are. <a href="../civil_de/civil_1.html-ssi">Surprised us big time!</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI>Bootleg U2 Music on the Internet. <a href="../class_2/class2_8.html-ssi">Curiouser and Curiouser.</a><BR>
