 <H4>11/14/96</H4>

 <LI>Defense Science Board Task Force on Information Warfare-Defense 
(IW-D), will be issuing a report in the next few days.  Federal Computer Week 
has an interesting article stating that the report called the threat of an IW 
attack "significant," adding that the nation's "vulnerabilities are numerous, 
[and] the countermeasures are extremely limited...." You can read the article at <a href="http://www.fcw.com/pubs/fcw/1111/duck.htm">http://www.fcw.com/pubs/fcw/1111/duck.htm</a>. We will be publishing the report as it is made available to us.<BR>
<BR>

<LI><a href="http://www.asiatimes.com/96/10/29/29109618.html">Armageddon in Cyberspace</a>, by Doug Tsuruoka, Asia Times. Some of the 
quotes are a bit off, but hey, that's the press. <BR>
<BR>
<LI> A controversial proposal to extend/create new <a href="../class_2/class2_7.html-ssi">copyright laws.</a><BR>
<BR>

 <H4>11/13/96</H4>
<LI><a href="http://www.cdi.org/mailing/russia/">Johnson's Russia List Archive</a> Mailing list archive from David Johnson of the Center for Defense
Information, Washington, DC.  Provides a wealth of articles,
covering news and views of contemporary Russia with particular
emphasis on political developments.<BR>

Thanks to Jim Easton: <a href="MAILTO:jeaston@johannsen.com">jeaston@johannsen.com</a><BR>
