 <H4>11/05/96</H4>
 <LI><a href="../resource/res_8.html-ssi">"Gulf War Syndrome"</a> We were asked to help out with the GulfLINK Files. Previously classified, these documents give extensive background on the Gulf War and 
potential exposure by US troops to chemical or biological agents. All 308 of the 
files are now available for download as a single extracting executable.  (480K)<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="../class_3/class3_k.html-ssi">WEAPONS OF MASS DESTRUCTION IN TERRORISM</a>   The Emerging Threat Posed by Non-State Proliferation.  Cmdr. Campbell
states,..." To date most informed opinions on non-state political violence
suggest that terrorist of the future will neither seek to develop, nor
threaten to use weapons of mass destruction (WMD)."  Exellent reading.<BR>
