<H4>Postings of Note from 09/96</H4>

<H4>09/30/96</H4>
 <LI>"New Crypto-Attack Weakens Seeming Strength in Smart Cards, Secure ID 
Cards, or Vale Cards.  <a href="../infosec/infosec4.html-ssi">This Article</a> from Bellcore should be Required Reading."<BR>
<BR>
<H4>09/29/96</H4>
<LI>By John Dermaut, <a href="../class_3/class3_7.html-ssi">DISTURBING "DEJA ENTENDU"AND "DEJA VU".</a> This article was written assuming that the TWA 800 plane was downed by an explosive device.<BR>
<BR>

<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4ie.html-ssi">"Information War and Some Aspects of A Computer Operator's Defense"</a> by, Victor I. Sointev, Ph.D. An interesting paper by one of  Moscow's
leading professors that was presented at InfoWarCon5.<BR>

<BR>
<LI>You can hide yourself, but it takes time and effort, <a href="../class_1/class1_e.html-ssi">and sometimes
you walk a fine line</a><BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/28/96</H4>

<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4id.html-ssi">"First Steps Toward a Defense"</a> by Michael Wilson. Wilson clearly demonstrates that we can mount defensive information warfare.  We just have to start!<BR>
<BR>

<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4ic.html-ssi">"New World Vistas - Air and Space Power For The 21st Century".</a>  A comprehensive report by the Air FOrce Scientific Advisory Board that identify technologies that will guarantee the air and space authority of the United States.<BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/27/96</H4>
<LI>By Capt. Roger D. Thrasher, USAF:  <a href="../mil_c4i/thesis.pdf"> "Information Warfare:
Implications For Forging The Tools."</a> (in PDF file Format) Direct your comments to Capt. Thrasher at:  <a href="MAILTO:thrasher@RL.AF.Mil">thrasher@RL.AF.Mil</a><BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/25/96</H4>
<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4ib.html-ssi">"Hardwar, Softwar, Wetwar: Operational Objectives of Information Warfare"</a> by Michael Wilson, The Nemesis Group. Read about the "value chain"...an
aggregate infrastructure of processes, best explained by example.<BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/23/96</H4>
<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4ia.html-ssi">"CORNERSTONES OF INFORMATION WARFARE"</a> The Information Age is also transforming all military operations by
providing commanders with information unprecedented in quantity and quality.
The commander with the advantage in observing the battlespace, analyzing
events, and distributing information possesses a powerful, if not decisive,
lever over the adversary.  Ronald R. Fogleman, General, USAF   and    Sheila
E. Widnall Secretary of the Air Force.<BR>
<BR>
<H4>09/21/96</H4>
<LI>Your ISP is like your doctor or lawyer. <a href="../class_1/class1_d.html-ssi">Are they maintaining your 
privacy?<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="../class_1/class1_c.html-ssi">GERMAN GOVERNMENT</a> PUSHES BLOCKAGE OF NETHERLANDS WEB SITES.<BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/19/96</H4>
<LI><img border=0 src="../class_1/coolhot.gif"> Hackers crack <a href="../hacker/hack4.html-ssi">CIA home page code.</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4i9.html-ssi"> "Managing INFOWAR in the Future"</a>,  by Arnold E. Donahue.  Where should the leadership and stewardship of the multi-faceted efforts that make up the offensive and defensive parts of INFOWAR be housed?  Who should be the head honcho of these efforts?  <BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/17/96</H4>

<LI> Call for Papers for <a href="../papers/paper_1.html-ssi">InfoWarCon 6, Sixth International Conference on Information Warfare and Systems Assurance</a> Brussels, Belgium May 4-6, 1997.<BR>
<BR>
 <LI> SOLDIER-SCHOLAR is a bi-annual journal of contemporary military thought  published by the Military Art and Science faculty at the US Air Force  Academy.   We are currently seeking <a href="../papers/paper_3.html-ssi">paper submissions</a> for our Fall 1996  issue focusing on Warfare in the Information Age.<BR>

<H4>09/16/96</H4>

<LI>Atlanta NRC Cryptography Briefing <a href="../resource/conf4.html-ssi">"Cryptography's Role in Securing the Information Society"</A> Presentation on October 21, 1996 by Dr. Herb Lin of the National Research Council<BR>
<BR>

<LI> By Christine A.R. McNulty <a href="../class_1/class1_b.html-ssi">"Changing Values and Their Implications for the Ethics of Information Warfare."</a> The information revolution has given us all manner of wonderful things, but it has also created a monster - information warfare.  At its heart, information warfare is about people - as individuals and organizations. McNulty presents a clear picture at what we are actually prepared to do; to what degree are we willing to be other than "nice guys", and to what degree
are we willing to give up aspects of our own freedom in the name of security.<BR>

<H4>09/15/96</H4>

<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4i8.html-ssi">"The E-Bomb- a Weapon of Electrical Mass Destruction."</a> by Carlo Kopp.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="../resource/res_2.html-ssi">CIABASE</A> is a computer data base on the Central Intelligence.<BR>
<BR>
<LI>Presented at InfoWarCon96, Professor Dr. D.S. Chereshkin's <a href="../mil_c4i/Doclusa.doc">"Realities of InfoWars"</a> a brief thesis from the distinguished Vice President of the Russian Academy of Natural Science, Moscow, Russia. (322K DOC Format)<BR>
<BR>
<LI>Russian views on Infosecurity.  Prof. Vitaly Tsygichko, prof.Dmitry Chereshkin, prof. Georgy Smolian. <a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4i7.html-ssi">"ESTIMATION OF EFFICIENCY FOR INFORMATION SECURITY SYSTEMS"</a> <BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/14/96</H4>

<LI><a href="../class_3/class3_6.html-ssi">Denial of Service</a> Hits NY ISP.<BR>
<BR>

<LI>Lettermans <a href="../humor/humor3.html-ssi">Top 10 things</a> that sound dirty at the office, but aren't:<BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/13/96</H4>

 <LI>ENN reports on <a href="../class_3/class3_5.html-ssi">security issues</a> at Newark International Airport.<BR>
<BR>
 <LI> Hacker Alert!  Don't miss this! <a href="../hacker/hack3.html-ssi">OSS'96</a><BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/11/96</H4>
 <LI> "Security in Cyberspace", a comprehensive 63 page report from the
Senate Committee on Governmental Affairs.  There is a lot here.... a good
read. This can be found at :  <a href="http://www.senate.gov/~gov_affairs/dem/psi/hearings/960522/gaosum.htm">URL</a> and then Link to: <a href="http://www.senate.gov/~gov_affairs/">http://www.senate.gov/~gov_affairs/</a><BR>

<BR>
<H4>09/10/96</H4>
 <LI>From PC Week Online, How to to turn an <a href="../infosec/infosec3.html-ssi">NT Workstation into a NT Server.</a><BR>
<BR>

<LI>China Limits <a href="../class_3/class3_4.html-ssi">Internet Connections.</a> Thank you ENN.<BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/09/96</H4>
<LI> Lexis-Nexis sells a commercial database called "Ptrax" which holds detailed personal information on nearly all Americans (L-N claims it contains 300 million names). This describes how to <a href="../class_1/class1_9.html-ssi">remove your name</a> from it. <BR>
<BR>
<LI>THE SEVENTH CONFERENCE ON COMPUTERS, FREEDOM, AND PRIVACY <a href="../resource/conf3.html-ssi">Call for Participation.</A> March 11-14, 1997<BR>
<BR>

<LI>Pro-Privacy Encryption Legislation: <img border=0 src="../class_1/coolhot.gif"><a href="../class_1/class1_a.html-ssi">Your Help is Needed NOW!</a><BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/07/96</H4>

<LI>Issues from the <a href="http://www.infowar.com/iwftp/cloaks/cloaks.html-ssi">Cloaks and Daggers Digest</A><BR>

<H4>09/06/96</H4>

<LI>Issues from the <a href="http://www.infowar.com/iwftp/risks/risks-18/index_18.html-ssi">Risks Digest Volume 18</A> in HTML format.<BR>

<H4>09/04/96</H4>

<LI>By Robert David Steele-Vivas, founder of Open Source Solutions, Inc. <a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4i6.html-ssi">"Creating a Smart Nation"</a> will illustrate to you how the United States needs
to approach: Strategy, Policy, Intelligence and Information. This will get your wheels moving!<BR>
<BR>

<LI><a href="../class_1/class1_8.html-ssi">Spam lists.</a> <BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/03/96</H4>

<LI><a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4i5.html-ssi">"The Essence of Warfare - A Return To First Principals"</a> by
Michael Wilson of the Nemesis Group.  It is no surprise, that some basic principles behind the Art or Science of War are becoming more evident as we once again transform our ways of thinking on the subject.<BR>
<BR>

<LI><a href="../class_3/class3_3.html-ssi">"The Precipice Problem: A Guide to the Destabilization of Western Civilization"</a>  by  Michael Wilson of the The Nemesis Group talks about Denial of Service.<BR>
<BR>

   <LI>An article by one of the most outstanding women in the field of Information Warfare.  Dr. Elin Whitney-Smith of  George Washington University shows how it is necessary to *connect* people to an individual source of information that will ultimately foster economic, political development and individual identity.  Don't miss <a href="../class_1/class1_7.html-ssi">"Information Revolutions, National Security and Individual Consciousness: Changing Paradigms."</a><BR>
<BR>

<LI>Particpate in the ISS (Information Systems Security) Survey.  This information will be compiled and return to the Senate Permanent Subcommittee on Invesitigations.  It is anonymous!  Your input is VALUED. <a href="iss_surv.doc">Downloadable in Word 6.0 format</a>.
<BR>
<PRE>You can Snail Mail the form to:   
                  Mark Gembecki
                  WarRoom Research
                  1134 Veranda Court
                  Baltimore, MD  21226-2211
                  Phone: 410-437-1106 Fax: 410-437-1118
OR E-Mail to:     WarRoom2@aol.com    
</PRE>
<BR>

<H4>09/02/96</H4>

<LI>A new Public-Key Encryption Scheme? Taking on the giant RSA? A new patent pending PK system has just been announced and the New Zealand inventors claim it offers vast improvements over the current 
methods. For more informaton on RPK Encryption scheme. Check out their claims about export control, too. <a href="http://crypto.swdev.co.nz"> http://crypto.swdev.co.nz</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI>This paper will examine a new threat and highly unconventional military environment, discussing the challenges facing the tactical and strategic military environments as they conduct operations in the <a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4i4.html-ssi">Fifth Dimension of Warfare</a>. Written by Richard F. Forno .<BR>
<BR>

<LI>Maximizing the flow and control of information is key to competitiveness, whether it be on the battlefield, in the marketplace, or on the campaign trail.  An innovative tool and approach to planning and managing intelligence or information in these very intense, time sensitive environments is the <a href="../mil_c4i/mil_c4i3.html-ssi">"WarRoom".</A> by Mark Gembecki and Steven Shaker.<BR>
<BR>

<H4>09/01/96</H4>
 <LI>Anon.Penet.Fi Anonymous remailer to be closed. "This is indeed a sad day in history of the Net," one comment begins. <a href="../class_1/class1_6.html-ssi">Read why.</a> <BR>
<BR>





<P>We'll do our best to keep you informed of new and exciting postings on Infowar.Com. We might miss a few, so regular scanning of the site is probably a good idea. This page starts out empty - but look around and see what we've begun with. And then . . .<a href="MAILTO:webwarrior@infowar.com">Contribute your work</A> so we can share it with other InfoWarriors. Many thanks in advance.</P>

