<center><h3>
Military Pages Off Internet After Hack Attempt

  <BR>

</h3>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<P>December 31, 1996
 
<P>    WASHINGTON (Reuter) - Most Defense Department information was pulled off the
Internet world-wide computer network Sunday after a hacker break-in attempt
damaged an Air Force page, the service said Monday.
<P>     The Air Force said most of the information was expected to be back on the
network late Monday.
<P>     The Defense Department has more than 80 World Wide Web sites on the public
Internet including a Gulf War Illness site, information about each of the
military services, press releases and military contract announcements.
<P>     The Air Force said most of the web sites were taken off the Internet after
a hacking attempt destroyed its home page, the page that guides computer users
to Air Force information available on the computer network.
<P>     It said federal authorities were investigating.
    
Copyright 1996 Reuters Ltd.  All rights reserved.</P>

