<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/pent.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>

</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<h3><Center>Infiltrations at military facilities.   Received on G-Two.<BR>

</H3>

<BR>
</Center>

</table>
<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<td width=440>

December 28, 1996<BR><BR>

<P>
The need for security varies due to the threat climate at various US military
facilities. Most of the time we worry about the threat of infiltration or
intelligence collections or foreign agents or terrorists. In the mid 1970s
and even into the early 1980s, military SpecOps personnel and  Special Agents
were tasked by the Pentagon to infiltrate bases overseas and in the US as a
test of US security forces. In some cases agents were able to gain access to
nuclear weapon storage areas. In other infiltrations the agents entered the
military bases in a very overt style. The Palestinian head dress and a green
fatigue clothing was worn in some tests. In other tests agents wearing Soviet
uniforms entered the bases through the front gate and received a smart salute
from the guards. Often a limo was rented by the agent personnel who put a
flashing red light on the roof and a small flag taped to the front bumper. I
performed many such infiltrations through Europe and the Middle East and even
in the US. I will say that in 75 tests carried out in the US, our teams were
able to roll through with PLO or Russian uniforms and our VIP looking status
symbol-the limo. The one exception was the USMC facility at 29 Palms in
California where a Marine did not care if he offended anyone and nearly shot
both me and another counterintelligence CT/AT agent ! After our
explainations, our credentials and badges, and a letter from the JCS we were
able to get off the asphalt and and file a favorable report on the perimeter
security of this facility !

<P>These penetrations were the idea of the JCS at the Pentagon after they had
admitted the security forces might be lax in some services. The "Red Cell"
operations carried out later by SEALs were basically the same idea-infiltrate
and then get the troops motivated to increase the idea or theory of security.
Our early attempts consisted of climbing fences, passing through sensor
areas, "sneaking and peeking", and leaving proof of our access to "secure
sites". In one case I was able to autograph a nuclear device due to a very
laid back civilian GSA guard force. Simulated IEDs were placed on or near oil
storage tanks, the base commanders home, the base security police
building,etc. After early 1982 we stopped the penetrations feeling that we
had enhanced the overall security posture of the facilities we had tested.
Commanders called us a variety of names claiming we  "did not play fair" in
that we sent no warning to the facility we were coming. Terrorists don't
either. Today we still see pizza delivery cars, taxis, and UPS trucks waved
through gates with little or no checking.

<P>The tests are to begin again. Teams from the Defense Special Weapons Agency
are to start infiltration of world wide sites in Jan 97 due to the incident
at the Khobar Towers. Although tests are done frequently at nuclear storage
facilities, most bases have not continued testing themselves. With a variety
of SpecOps personnel, investigators will again try to gain entry to US,
Middle Eastern, Asian, and European posts and bases. Due to my background in
performing these tests I hope everyone can perform like the Marine at 29
Palms. Terrorism can take place anywhere-anytime. Security is serious
business. This series of inspections can only aid our target hardening by
pointing out problem areas. 

<P>I would suppose there will be some people again claiming this to be unfair.
But as we all know, real terrorists foreign and domestic do not always play
fair.

<P>Paul Copher<BR>
Tucson


<P>Added Post:<BR>
Date: Sat, 28 Dec 1996 01:25:16 -0500<BR>
From: PaulC76504@aol.com<BR>
Message-ID: <961228012516_1155717973@emout18.mail.aol.com><BR>
To: betty@infowar.com<BR>
Subject: Re: Infiltrations at military facilities

<P>All police facilities are stressing polite contact. Last time I took 10 guys inside a
classifed site by riding in back of a UPS truck. The driver thought it was a
big joke. What upsets me are the taxis and pizza deliveries. You can even
ride one into the CIA driven by a foreign and illegal driver.

<P>Paul Copher</P>

</td>

