<tr>
<td width=440>
December 23, 1996
<BR>
<P>Merry Christmas.  I thought you might enjoy this forward from Walt Coleman.</P>

<CENTER>                      Doorbell rings, I'm not list'nin',<BR>
                     From my mouth, drool is glist'nin',<BR>
                              I'm happy--although<BR>
                              My boss let me go--<BR>
                          Happily addicted to the Web.<BR>
<BR>
                        All night long, I sit clicking,<BR>
                            Unaware time is ticking,<BR>
                           There's beard on my cheek,<BR>
                            Same clothes for a week,<BR>
                          Happily addicted to the Web.<BR>
<BR>
                        Friends come by; they shake me,<BR>
                               Saying, "Yo, man!<BR>
                   Don't you know tonight's the senior prom?"<BR>
                   With a listless shrug, I mutter, "No, man;<BR>
                     I just discovered letterman-dot-com!"<BR>
<BR>
                        I don't phone, don't send faxes,<BR>
                         Don't go out, don't pay taxes,<BR>
                              Who cares if someday<BR>
                               They drag me away?<BR>
                       I'm happily addicted to the Web!<BR>

</CENTER>
<BR>
Best Regards,<BR>

Mike<BR>

