<tr>
<td width=440>

<h3><Center>National Defense University releases <BR>highly critical report of info ops in Bosnia.<BR>

By Bryan Bender</H3>

<BR>
</Center>

</table>
<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<td width=440>

December 20, 1996<BR><BR>

<P>
Bob Brewin <<A HREF="MAILTO:brewin@access.digex.net">brewin@access.digex.net</A>>
<P>Folks -- NDU has just released a highly critical report of info ops in
Bosnia, saying among other things the info does not flow very well below
brigade level. Also report says over half the computers there have
viruses. 

<P>You can find it on the Web on the National Defense U. Web site, in
the Strategic Forums session, ``Information Operations In Bosnia'',
autjored by a recently retired Col. Kenneth Allard. You can find it at:
<A HREF="HTTP://198.80.36.91/ndu/inss/strforum/forum91.html">http://198.80.36.91/ndu/inss/strforum/forum91.html</A>

<P>Bob Brewin<BR>
editor-at-large<BR>
(whatever that means)<BR>
Federal Computer Week</P>

</td>

<td width=80>
