<IMG ALT="[Bomb2]" SRC="../../images/bomb2_li.gif" width=580><p>


<!-- Article Body Table ---------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/class2.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>
<P>UK: NEWS - POLITICIANS AWAIT FRESH ATTACKS ON WEB SITES<BR>

  <BR>

</h3>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<P>December 19, 1996
 
<P> A hacker in the US could attack other UK political party Web sites in the wake
of the attack on the Labour Party's site. New Media Age has received information
that the hacker may target the Conservative Party site next. Labour's site was
taken offline on Tuesday and police called in after two raids on the site.
The source said: "It is someone trying to express their political freedom. They
are looking to target other sites, like the Conservatives."
A spokesman for Online Publishing, which designed the site, said the hack was
expertly done. Despite press reports to the contrary, he said no password
compromise took place.
<P>The Web site was altered on Saturday evening, but the changes only lasted for 20
minutes before Potptel, which hosts the site, managed to refresh the site.
Malcolm Corbett, Poptel's marketing director, confirmed the attack and said
Poptel was investigating security measures.
Security on the Conservative Party site has also been stepped up since the
attack, according to Peter Collingwood of WebWorks, its developers.
While not yet under direct attack, the Party's site
(<A HREF="HTTP://www.conservative-party.org.uk">www.conservative-party.org.uk</A>) is being aped by a rival site called
Conservative Information (<A HREF="HTTP://www.conservative.org.uk">www.conservative.org.uk</A>). Choosing the link `A Party
to Believe In' takes a user to the Referendum Party site.
<P>Copyright 1996 Centaur Communications Limited or its licensors. <BR>
ADVERTISING/MARKETING/MEDIA <BR>
NEW MEDIA AGE 12/12/96 P2 </P>

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
