<IMG ALT="[Bomb2]" SRC="../../images/bomb2_li.gif" width=580><p>


<!-- Article Body Table ---------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/question.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<H3>
<CENTER>SOURCES eJOURNAL announces <BR>
SOURCES BRIEFINGS, <BR>
A new bi-weekly cutting edge intelligence report.</CENTER>
</h3>



</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>
<BR>
December 12, 1996<BR>
<BR>

<P>Featuring original investigation, reporting and
analysis, SOURCES BRIEFINGS is published by the same staff that produces
SOURCES eJOURNAL, the ONLY all-original electronic report on international
intelligence issues

<P>"Our stories and briefs are prepared by seasoned veteran correspondents and
intelligence and military analysts who provide exclusive, breaking
intelligence that will put you in front of the power curve," states
Publisher Glenn EJM Davis.

<P>SOURCES BRIEFINGS is already stacking up as a unique and highly focused
medium where subscribers get regular, hard-hitting, information-packed work
every two weeks. Says Managing Editor Anthony L. Kimery (formerly
Washington correspondent for the Paris-based Intelligence Newsletter), "We
cover everything from terrorism to the proliferation of weapons of mass
destruction; from organized crime to political crime; from behind the
scenes views of covert operations to the back-door wheeling and dealing of
defense contractors."

<P>SOURCES BRIEFINGS Issue I, Volume 1 reports on TERRORISM at home and
abroad: the threat of gang violence escalating to fifth column status in
the US with the help of agents of IRAN and the Nation of Islam; Mexican
GANGS living next to the US border receiving arms from sources in the
Middle East; SMUGGLERS coming across the Mexican border carrying
sophisticated weapons in back packs; PLO preparations for war; a senior
cleric in Iran issuing a "fatwa" threatening the government of Saudi
Arabia; the Iraqi state-run English language daily, Kayan International,
warning if "America's traditional disrespect for Muslim civilian life [does
not stop] without further delay... Muslims will be forced to find other
ways to make this point clear to US. leaders... and more.

<P>In BRIEFINGS section, COLLECTION, domestic imagery is reportedly at risk by
the Whitewater investigation. Other articles discuss a counterintelligence
investigation at the White House, a Congressional review of SAPS (Special
Access Programs - military black bag operations); and the relevancy of the
Foreign Intelligence Advisory Board.

<P>Under COVERT OPS, SOURCES BRIEFINGS examines CIA and House Banking
Committee probes of MENA and together with an Inslaw Update, expands on
SOURCES eJOURNAL's year-long coverage of these two currently breaking
stories. Look for information on the Pentagon's new spy agency; CIA's
handling of NOCs (Non-Official Cover organizations); a morale problem in
Special Forces; and secret U.S. arms caches in Europe.

<P>Under ORGANIZED CRIME, and DRUG TRAFFICKING & MONEY LAUNDERING, are reports
on US. concerns about growing Russian corruption, and DEA probes that have
recently re-activated Barry Seal's bank accounts. Under FOREIGN AFFAIRS,
SOURCES BRIEFINGS looks at Israel's secret PLO deals; secret meetings between
Israel and Jordan; danger facing Netanyahu in Egypt; Japan's negotiations
to remove Futenma Air Base... and more.

<P>SOURCES BRIEFINGS is published by SOURCES eJOURNAL, an on-line magazine
covering information, disinformation and intelligence featuring all
original reporting. The look and feel of the magazine calls to mind classic
journals like Harper's and Saturday Review. Recently SOURCES eJOURNAL was
awarded an OMNI Magazine Omnivision Award for Excellence in On-line
Journalism, and is listed at the top of USA Today's Interesting Places To
Go.


<P>SOURCES eJOURNAL can be accessed on the World Wide Web
(http://www.dso.com). SOURCES BRIEFINGS is available by fax or email at an
annual rate of $395. A semi-annual subscription is $250; a quarterly
subscription, $150. A pre-publication sample of SOURCES BRIEFINGS is
currently available for the asking.

<P>For samples and subscription information please email Joshua Rinsky at
sales@dso.com, or call (415) 981-6411; mail checks to DSO, Inc., 601 Van
Ness Ave., #E3425, SF CA 94102.

<P>DSO - a San Francisco Company since 1984 1996 DSO Inc.  All rights reserved.

<P> <A HREF="HTTP://www.dso.com">http://www.dso.com</A></P>

</td>
</tr>
</table>

