<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>
Denial of Service Attack at Univeristy<BR>

<BR>

</h3>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

Poster:  hawk christopher <a href="MAILTO:hawk1@ux1.cso.uiuc.edu">hawk1@ux1.cso.uiuc.edu</a><BR>
Subject: E-mail bombing prosecuted<BR>
------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>


<P>Saw an article in the local paper yesterday saying Illinois State
University, in Bloomington, IL, has a criminal case going against
someone for sending e-mail "bombs" to ISU computer systems.

<P>I don't have the article with me, but it said the suspect, a disgruntled
ex-student, set up a program to send hundreds and hundreds of e-mail
messages into ISU systems, causing them to slow or crash.  The bombs hit
ISU PD twice.  The suspect was identified by a staff member in the
residence hall department, who tracked down the source of the e-mail and
turned the info over to police.

<P>The suspect was charged with something like "criminal tampering with a
computer."

<P>Congratulations to ISU for this, and apologies to all for not having
details....I'll look for the article again later.<BR>
<BR>
--Chris<BR>
<BR>
<P>Officer Christopher Hawk University of Illinois PD

<P>**The University of Illinois doesn't pay me enough to express its
opinions. **<BR>

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
