<td valign=middle width=440>
</h2>


</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>

<center><H3><BR>
<B>
More on the FLT 800 Missile Thoery - A rebuttal</B>
</H3>
</center>
 Date: Fri, 15 Nov 1996 19:33:13<BR>
 From: Parveez Syed <parveez@cr78ra1uk.win-uk.net<BR>
 To: joeshea@netcom.com, parveez@cr78ra1uk.win-uk.net<BR>
 Subject: Re: The Missile theory<BR>
<BR>
 Friday 15 Nov 1996, London-UK<BR>
<BR>
 Hello Joe Shea,<BR>
<BR>
<P> On Sat, 9 Nov 1996 at 14:23:29 -0800 (PST), you wrote:   ... "I am
editor of The American Reporter, a daily newspaper on the Internet.  I
would like to ask you if, indeed, you were the person who was the first
to post a note concerning the possibility that a missile strike may have
been responsible for   the shooting down of TWA Flight 800. I can find
no earlier  mention of that possibility than your July 22 posts to CPSR.
  I would appreciate your urgent response, as i was unable to contact
you by telephone (I got a "switched off" message). "

<P> I am editor-producer of Shanti RTV news agency in London, UK.  I
verified the positions of the US navy within the firing range  in the
area at the time of the "friendly-fire", and reported the  findings
within hours with update on 22 July 96. I am sorry about  this delay in
reply. I was repeatedly  hospitalised after massive  heart attack on
Saturday 03 Aug 96.  I was discharged from my  local hospital this
afternoon. The "friendly-fire" possibility was  totally ingnored by most
mainstream media groups for almost ten  weeks. Shanti RTV tries harder
to be first with the news without  mainstream media resources and
fundings!

<P> Now please allow me to correct your Clark Staten's published  report
dated Friday 08 Nov 1996. Staten's report, it seems, is  based on ERRI's
libelous and defamatory disinformation and their  alleged probe.
Firstly, I am not "Parveez Syad", and I am now  known as "Parveez
Hussein". I have never "operated" from  Birmingham, England. I am not
subject of any government  investigation. I am not an Iranian. I was
never an Iranian  national. I am not an Iranian propagandist or
extremist. The  ERRI is spreading libelous, slanderous disinformation.
So, what  is their real, hidden agenda? Why are they trying to shift
focus  away from the possibility of "friendly-fire"? Are they trying to
refute or discredit Pierre Salinger? Why? Why are they and your
publication trying to mis-spell my name? What is their/your  real,
hidden motive?

<P>So, who is going to apologies for the coherent disinformation campaign
by the intelligence agencies and their assets?</P>

Kind regards<BR>
<BR>
 Parveez Syed<BR>
Shanti RTV news<BR>
============================================================<BR>
<BR>
Editorial Reply; An open letter to Mr. Syed<BR>
<BR>
<P>Thank you, Mr. Syed, for confirming the main assertion of our story that
you were the FIRST person to make "friendly fire" allegations in regard
to the tragic crash of TWA Flight 800.  It is interesting, indeed, that
you freely admit that within hours of the disaster, and again on July
22, 1996, without any shred of visible evidence, that you were making
allegations that a U.S. Army or U.S. Navy missile took the lives of 230
American and French citizens.

<P>In regard to your charges that you are not an "Iranian" or "Iranian
national," the intent of our our reference was not necessarily to
reflect your country of ethnic origin or nationality, but rather that
you are/were acting for, or on behalf of Iran or other Islamic
Fundamentalists.  A review of your website and various writings,
distributed to hundreds by e-mail and fax, would confirm for the
discerning reader that you have been engaged for some time in a
questionable, on-going campaign of anti-American, anti-Israel, and
anti-Jewish rhetoric.  That. by definition, is "propaganda."

<P>In regard to your charges, Mr. Syed,  that ERRI is attempting to spread
"libelous, slanderous disinformation," and that we have a "hidden
agenda," in regard to the TWA Flight 800 disaster, we would only suggest
that the reader review our previous factual reports in this area.  We
believe that any unbiased review of the available facts will reveal that
your Flight 800 allegations are intended to misdirect the reader to
unsubstantiated, baseless, and ill-advised conclusions.  You should
know, that in the United States (and most of the rest of the world),
that nothing is libelous or slanderous if it is truthful.

<P>Finally, Mr. Syed, it is clear that you have attempted to discredit the
government of the United States and her allies, and to spread fear and
mistrust in America, for some time. This latest, transparent, and
scurrilous attempt to blame the deaths of the passengers of Flight 800
on our government has failed...as well it should.  In the process, you
have exacerbated the pain and anguish of the families and friends of
those killed in the Flight 800 disaster. We will leave it to the reader
to ask...what is YOUR motive in charging our government with killing its
own citizens?  Is it an unbiased attempt to present the facts, or an
attempt to shield those that may have perpetrated this atrocity? If it
is the former...where are the facts or any evidence to support your
allegations?

<P>Respectfully,</P>

Clark Staten, Executive Director<BR>
EmergencyNet News Service<BR>
Emergency Response & Research Institute<BR>


</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
