<P>12.  Jeffrey A. Builta, Extremist Groups:  An International Compilation of Terrorist Organizations, Violent Political Groups, and Issue Oriented Militant Movements,  John Murray and Richard H. Ward, eds., (Chicago, Ill:  The Office of International Criminal Justice, 1996), 663-675, 725-823, 1039-1115.  Since 1983 over 50,000 people have been killed adjunct to violence in Sri Lanka.
