<!-- Article Body Table ---------------------------------------------->

<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<img border=0 width=43 height=43 src="../../images/lock.gif">
</td>
<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h3>

PKZip Trojan Horse....<BR>
Distribute to your security personnel.

</h3>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>
<P>     SUBJ: COMPUTER SECURITY (COMPUSEC) ADVISORY 95-21//</P>
     
<P>     1. PROBLEM:  TROJAN HORSE VERSION OF PKZIP IS AVAILABLE ON THE 
     INTERNET.</P>
<P>     2. DAMAGE: DESTRUCTION OF HARD DISK FILES BY REFORMATTING 
     THE HARD DISK.</P>
<P>     3. DESCRIPTION: THE FILES PKZ300B.ZIP AND PKZ300B.EXE ARE BEING 
     ADVERTISED AS NEW VERSIONS OF PKZIP.  YOUR HARD DISK WILL BE 
     REFORMATTED AS YOU WAIT FOR THE INSTALL PROGRAM TO EXECUTE. THE 
     REFORMATTING IS TRANSPARENT TO THE USER. ONCE THE INSTALL PROGRAM 
IS 
     COMPLETED A MESSAGE WILL BE DISPLAYED INDICATING THAT YOUR HARD 
DISK 
     HAS BEEN REFORMATTED. </P>
 <P>    4. SOLUTION: DO NOT EXECUTE THESE FILES. THE CURRENT AUTHORIZED 
     VERSION OF PKZIP IS PK204G. FOR MORE DETAILS ON THIS 
VULNERABILITY, </P>
     PLEASE CONTACT NAVCIRT.
<P>     5. NAVCIRT WOULD LIKE TO ACKNOWLEDGE THE EFFORTS OF PKWARE INC. 
IN 
     RESEARCHING THIS VULNERABILITY AND MAKING THIS INFORMATION 
AVAILABLE. </P>
<P>     6. PLEASE DISTRIBUTE THIS INFORMATION TO INDIVIDUALS WHO
     IMPLEMENT SECURITY POLICY AND PROCEDURES WITHIN YOUR ACTIVITY</P>

<BR>


<BR>

</td>

