<td valign=middle width=440>
<center><h2>

 For anyone interested in information systems 
security news from Central & Eastern Europe
</h2>


</Center>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=440>
<P>IntelliTech has launched Central & East European Secure Systems
Strategies (CEESSS), an electronic periodical delivered three times
per week via e-mail and the Web to leading information systems
security professionals worldwide with active interest in developments
in Central & Eastern Europe (CEE), including Albania, Armenia,
Azerbaijan, Belarus, Bulgaria, Croatia, Czech Republic, Estonia,
Georgia, Hungary, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Latvia, Lithuania,
Macedonia, Moldova, Poland, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia,
Slovenia, Tajikstan, Turkmenistan, Ukraine, and Uzbekistan. Since
CEESSS' introduction on June 17, 1996, the periodical has received
great interest from readers worldwide, especially amongst information
technology (IT) vendors selling into the CEE markets, VARs, Systems
Integrators, consultants, commercial organizations, governments,
military and law enforcement.

<P>CEESSS covers topics including development of information security
strategies and policies, securing information systems and
communications channels from various attackers, counter-espionage
measures, advanced surveillance and countersurveillance technologies,
information warfare, civil-military national defense,
counter-terrorism measures, encryption, privacy, identification
systems, smart cards, electronic commerce and various topics related
to doing business in a world increasingly dominated by networked
information systems.

<P>To subscribe to the executive overview only version, send "subscribe
ceesss-eo your-e-mail-address" to "ceesss-eo-request@intellitech.cz"

<P>- Steven Slatem, Publisher, Editorial Director, Central & East
European Secure Systems Strategies (CEESSS), IntelliTech s.r.o.,
sslatem@intellitech.cz<BR>


<BR>

</td>

<td width=80>
<br>
</td>
