<h2><Center>The Militarily Critical Technologies List</H2>

<BR>
</Center>

</table>
<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<td width=440>

November 18, 1996<BR><BR>

<P></P>
<CENTER><img src="mctl.gif" alt="MCTL Icon"></CENTER>
<p></p>
<I>The Militarily Critical Technologies List (MCTL), is a detailed and
structured compendium of the technologies the Department of
Defense (DoD)  assesses as critical to maintaining superior
United States military capabilities.<br>
</I><p></p>
</center>
<P></P>
<img src="rainline.gif" alt="Multicolored Line">
<p></p>
<P>If you want to order a paper copy of this publication, go to link: 

<P><a href="http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/docorderform.html">http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/docorderform.html</a>  and pay $25.00 ( or download for free here)

<P><a href="http://www.dtic.mil/mctl/suggestionbox.html">http://www.dtic.mil/mctl/suggestionbox.html</a> - for comments regarding this document.

<P><a href="http://www.dtic.mil/mctl/">http://www.dtic.mil/mctl/</a> the Home Page of the Defense Technical Information Center.
<P><b> Documents are in Acrobat (*.pdf) Format </b>To view and display
these documents, you need an Adobe Acrobat viewer.  Adobe has FREE
Acrobat Reader software available that you can download <a
href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/readstep.html">for Macintosh,
Windows, MS-DOS and Sun Unix.</a></P>
<P>Download here <a href="http://www.infowar.com/iwftp/utils/acroread.zip">ACROREAD.ZIP</A> 
Acrobat PDF Viewer Ver 2.1 for Windows.
<P></P>
Should you have any questions or problems configuring your browser to
work in conjunction with the Acrobat reader, please refer to these
<a href="http://home.netscape.com/assist/helper_apps/shorthelper.html"> Instructions </a>
