<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<td width=440>

November 02, 1996<BR><BR>

<P>On 30 October, the USAF's first Information Warfare Training Laboratory,
Goodfellow AFB, Texas, was opened in a ceremony by General Billy Boles,
Commander, Air Education & Training Command.  On hand were the 17th Training
Wing and 17th Training Group commanders, COLs Kelvin Coppock and Ron Yaggi.
The lab, which will teach both offensive and defensive aspects of IW, was
built with technical expertise furnished by the Air Force Information
Warfare Center, Kelly AFB, Texas.</P>

