<tr>
<td width=440>

<h2><Center><B>INFORMATION  WAR  AND  SOME  ASPECTS OF  A  COMPUTER  OPERATOR'S  DEFENSE</B><BR></H2>
<h3>by Victor I. Solntsev, Ph.D.<BR><BR>
Associate Professor
Moscow State Technical University n.a. Bauman,<BR>
Russian Academy of Natural Sciences<BR>
</H3></Center>

</table>
<table width=580 border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2 valign=top width=60 align=right>
<td width=440>
<P>
<BR>
Download "Paper in Russian" <a href="Tez_warr.doc">Word Document</a> (32K)

<P>
Nowadays it's the beginning of a new age - the age of information
civilization, the age of open community. We have less then half
a decade to go into the third Millennium.
<P>
The main theme of this conference InfoWarCon 5 - electronic civil
defense - is rather urgent. Not long ago the priority of using
computer systems was fixed by military and scientific institutes.
Now it has passed in the hands of civil population. All of us
are users of computers: politicians, militaries, businessmen,
scientists, practically every person and even children. Advantages
of using a computer today are out of question. However potential
dangers and threats from using modern computer technologies have
a global scale.
<OL>
<LI>The Information reality and the problem of personal security
</OL>

<P>
Almost all activity of a person now is mediated by machines. That's
the point why our civilization is determined now as human-machine
civilization. Thus, the person becomes a component, factor of
more common integrity, namely formed during last decade of the
information reality. The creation of this symbolic and spiritual
information reality is the expression of becoming of Noosphere
as a common knowledge and intellect of the planet. It is also
a law-governed consequence. This reality is available to each
one as a component of environments. And everyone is responsible
its cleanness and safety. This virtual psychological and informational
reality can become a special factor of mastering the evolution
of modern community in conditions of personal security maintenance.
<P>
The problem of informational and psychological safety of the person
is a component of the noospheric world outlook.
<OL>
<LI>Matter - Energy - Information - Knowledge - Wisdom
</OL>

<P>
&quot; We have forgotten the wisdom for the sake of knowledge,
we lose knowledge in streams of the information.&quot; This statement
made by T.Elliot is not only a poetic exaggeration. It is one
of global problems of our existence in Noosphere. Cognition of
nature is a condition of life and development of the person, so
the understanding of artificial reality is a condition of survival
in it.
<P>
It is necessary to get rid from the illusion, that possessing
the information is identical to knowledge, understanding and wisdom.
Now it's a situation, when we can say that the more we know the
less we understand. Thus transformation of mass media in the tools
of information war - is a superficial symptom of a more serious
illness of the mankind.
<P>
In such circumstances the paradigm shift is necessary: from the
information - to knowledge, from knowledge and intelligence -
to meta-knowledge and wisdom. Several decades ago it was a priority
of material resources (energetic, financial...). Today it is substituted
to a priority of human intelligence and information. Probably,
such a point of view on the Information Warfare will remove its
actuality in the nearest future as it was already done with Space
Warfare. However the problem of personal security of the person
will not be strike off the agenda.
<OL>
<LI>Information War and a person
</OL>

<P>
The InfoWar definition accepted on this conference covers a wide
spectrum of problems, which are connected to security of information.
But now we shall focus our attention at some methodological aspects
of protection users of computer from different effects it can
provide.
<P>
The people were and still remain the major strategic resources
of a nation. The threat to the person is considered to be a key
questions of national security.
<P>
The modern scientific data testify potential possibility of effecting
on complex technical objects (technosphere), on consciousness
of the person (psychosphere), and on group consciousness of a
community (noosphere) (fig.1). This can be done by technical and
psychotechnical means, including mass media and psychotechnologies.
<P>
We consider that correct diagnosis of the danger is the condition
of choosing the correct strategy of defense, or, at least, adaptation.
<OL>
<LI>Scientific approaches to the Computer Operator's Security
Problem
</OL>

<P>
The Computer Operator's Security Problem (the COS-problem) is
a multidisciplinary one. It states a great number of nontrivial
questions to the modern science. The traditional approach of natural
sciences does not cover a list of psychophysical phenomena, which
are connected to consciousness of the person and to psycho-physiological
state of an organism. Integrative efforts in different areas of
knowledge - physics, biology, psychology, cybernetics, philosophy
and religion - are needed (fig.2).
<P>
Physiological approach of traditional medicine considers a person
only as an organism - a closed system of organs. This can be illustrated
on fig.3. Modern natural - scientific representation of the person
consider him to be an open system, which communicates with environment
using material, energy and information flows. So it is better
to illustrate this by fig.4. As we can see there are also energetic
acupuncture channels, energetic centers - chacres and energy-information
field shell - aura. Such a picture can be obtained using special
registration devices, such as, for instance, photograph in high
frequency currents (Kirlian's method) and some others.
<P>
There are opinions of the scientists that there is a dynamically
stabile holographic structure around the body as a result of interference
of various sorts of radiation. This structure is connected to
internal systems of an organism also with external environment.
<P>
It is stated that we can effect on the given structure by means
of various radiation (electromagnetic, acoustic, and etc.) and
cause changes in psycho-physiological condition of an organism.
<OL>
<LI>The Computer Operator's Security Problem
</OL>

<P>
We can consider the security of an operator to be a condition
in which personal mentality, consciousness and organism is defended
from deliberate effect of physical and psychical factors of informational
and/or of energetic nature. This factors are representing a threat
to stable existence and steady development as of an individual,
groups of individuals, population, state and society (fig.5).
<OL>
<LI>Operator as the target of attack
</OL>

<P>
The human possibilities are determined by levels of physical,
mental, intellectual and spiritual potentialities. All of them
are considered as potential targets of possible attack through
a computer. Let us look in detail to some basic targets.
<OL>
<LI>Organism
</OL>

<P>
The effect can be targeted on various organs and systems of a
human body which are ensuring the vital ability of the person
as a biological organism. Brain, central nervous system, immune
system, also systems of breathing, blood circulation, reproduction
and other vital systems and organs can be exposed to attack (fig.3).
<OL>
<LI>Psychics: mentality, consciousness and subconsciousness
</OL>

<P>
The highest and most subtle forms of human activity - mentality,
consciousness - appear to be targets of effect. They aren't protected
from deliberate destructive effects.
<OL>
<LI>Typology of Computer - Operator effects
</OL>

<P>
Let us consider a general classification of all possible effects
on an operator (fig.6) in the system &quot;Person - Environment&quot;.
<P>
Effects can be of natural or artificial origin. We can consider
physical, biophysical effect of the environment to be natural
ones. Energetic, informational and combined (energy-informational)
are artificial effects. Effects can be deliberate and indeliberate
by its character, destructive, neutral or constructive by its
direction. Apparently, physical nature of certain effect is the
main classifying feature.
<P>
Therefore we can differ three main types of effects: energetic,
informational and combined ones: energy-informational.
<OL>
<LI>Energetic effects
</OL>

<P>
Under power effect we understand deliberate or indeliberate effect
of physical fields of a various origin (electromagnetic, gravitational,
acoustic and other fields), which have an ability to influence
on vital processes of a person (fig.7).
<P>
The target of such an effect is mainly the organism as a physical
body. Energetic effects can cause violation of normal functions
of organs and systems. The level of violation vary from decreasing
adaptive capacity, tissues destruction and even to death.
<P>
Powerful electromagnetic superhigh-frequency radiation, ionizing
rays can be examples of such an effect. Electromagnetic, radiological,
acoustic weapons are already realized as non-traditional &amp;
non-lethal means of InforWar. As we can imagine a computer can
be modified to be such a weapon but at some extent. Because it
has all types of energetic effects already built-in.
<OL>
<LI>Information effects
</OL>

<P>
The role of the information in man-machine interaction is extremely
great. Modern driver goes not by highway itself, but mostly by
symbolic signs near it. The car goes along the road, but the driver
goes along the &quot;information field&quot;. A pilot controls
the plane with a control panel. An astronaut need not to look
out of the rocket to control it. And so on and so forth... Operator
becomes the profession of the century as you can see.
<P>
The world appears in the form of diverse information flows. And
the main task of a person it to process it in most effective way.
Continuous information noise creates a dense shielding between
a person and true reality, which is substituted by virtual reality.
<P>
Informational effects are deliberate or indeliberate influence
on a person by transmitting information (signals, messages, items
of information, images etc.).
<P>
The main target of information effect is consciousness of a person
or a group of the people. It is possible to distort an objective
reality of the environment. There can be various objectives of
such a distortion: from modification of behavior (individual or
collective) up to pathological violation of mental ability of
the person.
<P>
Commercials on TV are a vivid example of information effect through
mass media. And we are successfully imposed to destructive models
of behavior (aggressive, sexual etc.).
<OL>
<LI>Energy-informational effect
</OL>

<P>
Energy-informational effects are deliberate or indeliberate effect
of physical fields of a various origin, modulated by semantic
information signals, which can be perceived by biological organisms.
<P>
All natural systems and organisms participate in process of energy-information
interactions. Human being and some technical systems also can
be a source of deliberate energy-information effects.
<P>
Organism of the person, and all levels of his psychics (mentality,
subconsciousness, consciousness, superconsciousness) are targets
of energy-information effects.
<P>
Energy-information effects can cause violation of physiological
and mental processes (disease, disorder of organs and systems
of an organism, modification of behavior, suppression of thinking,
manipulation with consciousness, Zombie-effects, psychopathology
and destruction of personality and other).
<P>
Remote psychokinetic effect on state of biological objects and
physical systems, influence on highest mental functions of vital
organisms, healing are reliable examples of energy-information
effect.
<OL>
<LI>The computer as the Information Warfare
</OL>

<P>
Today we know various methods of non-lethal effect based on energy-informational
nature of a person as physical, biological and social object.
In the Information Warfare arsenal they are described as non-traditional
types of weapon: electromagnetic weapon (microwaves EHF and ELF),
infrasonic acoustic bombs, laser weapon, computer viruses (fig.7).
Their application is possible during any stage of Information
War. Potentially, in the modern computer all these type of weapons
can be integrated. And a system effect is not equal to a simple
sum of components.
<OL>
<LI>The computer as an acoustic bomb
</OL>

<P>
Acoustic bomb and multimedia computer can provide acoustic waves
of low frequency, like that of an earthquake. They are capable
to cause a strong nausea. Internal ear and mechanism of balancing
are irritated. Moreover mechanical devices can be programmed on
a resonance ultrasonic or infrasonic oscillations.
<OL>
<LI>The computer as an electromagnetic weapon.
</OL>

<P>
The electromagnetic radiation in large cities has reached critical
levels. The All-world Public Health Organization had included
this problem in the list of the most urgent ones for the mankind.
A new factor of an environment - electromagnetic fields (EMF)
comes into being. Experts calls EMF an active environmental factor
with disastrous consequences for all living nature. EMF capacity
increased near the power transmissions, radio and TV stations,
communication and radiolocation means and computers certainly.
<P>
Spectral range of electromagnetic radiation from the computer
is rather wide - from low-frequency oscillations of a power current,
superhigh-frequency radiation of processor units up to visible
light and ionizing radiation of the screen. In the InfoWar period
it is quite probable to use the computer as an active radiator
through the global network.
<OL>
<LI>The computer as a psychophysical weapon
</OL>

<P>
Psychophysical weapon is a kind of sensation and fiction at once.
But still it is a strange to see a smoke without a fire for at
least half a century.
<P>
August 13, 1994. It was an accident in Voronezsh city. One user
of personal computer had lost his consciousness in less then twenty
minutes of working at it. His friend - a programmer - told that
he felt a strange feeling, as though he was wholly tightened inside
the computer screen with Norton Commander menu. Also he felt headache
and some noise in ears. It was almost impossible to go away, as
though it was a hypnoses. Luckily he managed to put off the computer.
His friend was dead some time later, not coming in consciousness.
The diagnosis was bleeding inside the brain (insult).
<P>
The cause of his death was a computer virus named &quot;666&quot;.
Experts determined, that it produces on the screen so called 25-th
frame with a special color combination, that can immerse the person
in the sort of hypnotic trans. Each 25-th frame the picture changes.
And subconscious perception of a new pattern results in arrhythmia
of heart activity. Blood pressure sharply increases, and then
falls also sharply. And blood-vessels of a brain can not withstand
those pulses.
<P>
Later near 50 similar cases of sudden death are registered. Wasn't
it an information weapon ?
<OL>
<LI>Basic defensive methods and means
</OL>

<P>
In order to maintain security it is necessary to know from what
and how to be defended. First it is necessary to explore possible
types of effect on a person through the computer. Then development
of registration and measuring technique is needed. And at last
we are to determine a nature of the effect in order to apply corresponding
defensive methods.
<OL>
<LI>Development of registration methods
</OL>

<P>
In the described case it was enough to apply anti-virus program
and methods of video-registration with strobing of video-signal.
<P>
Detection of energy-informational effects is much more complicated
because the most perfect sensors are capable to register radiation
with capacity of 10-14-16 Joule. According to assumptions of scientists
capacity of a characteristic radiation of living organisms is
less then 10-20-22 Joule. However there are several methods of
indirect measurement of extremely low capacity radiation. Here
is a result of one of them.
<P>
On an energy-informational scheme (fig.8) we can determine characteristic
phantom radiation of biological objects and radiation of technical
systems. We can also see zones of long-term staying of persons,
or communication tools and computer with strong information flows.
The description of an obtained image allows to make conclusions,
for example, about favorable or unfavorable effect of a computer
on a person, or even person to a person.
<OL>
<LI>Shielding
</OL>

<P>
The simplest method of protection from electromagnetic radiation
is shielding. Certainly we can not stay for a long time in Faraday
camera and we will not wear a leaden suit. A metalized cloth is
an effective shield from EMF of wide frequency range - from extremely
low to superhigh. Filters for computer displays made from &quot;Voskhod&quot;
cloth decreases EMF ten times more effective in comparison with
&quot;Energostar&quot; screen which is considered to be the best
one. It will be necessary to the professionals, who works constantly
on the computer, to wear suits or overall made from metallized
cloth. It is the most reliable protection. Offices pasted over
with such a cloth and curtains are protected from harmful effect.
Signals of &quot;radio-bugs&quot; will not go out of the room.
<P>
However, besides protecting body and face from electromagnetic
radiation, we have eyes and ears open for obtaining the information.
And not always the information is good to a person.
<OL>
<LI>Psychotechnologies
</OL>

<P>
Mastering the methods of psycho-physiological regulation and psycho-technologies
can become an effective individual protection. It is not a secret,
that a polygraph can be deceived  using special tricks of self-regulation.
Psychological methods can decrease efficiency of electro-acoustic
effect and a number of others.
<OL>
<LI>Personal safety in the National and International law.
</OL>

<P>
There is no public institution, which can inspect and control
destructive applications of computer - operator effects. The community
appears to be defenseless from methods, which can appear in the
hands of a criminal or a terrorist.
<P>
Certainly we can call applications of a computer effects in InfoWar
a humanistic weapon. But there can be no humanity in any weapon
at all. We hope, that UN will revise the list of prohibited sorts
of weapons, and this can eliminate the level of danger. We consider,
that it is necessary to raise a question about informational and
psychological security of computer users in the UN Security Council.
And such a representative conference as InfoWarCon 5 can be the
first to tell to a world community some consideration about the
problem.
<P>
Admiral Vladimir Pirumov, the Head of the Scientific Council of
Security Council of Russian Federation and Vice-President of Russian
Academy of Natural Sciences consider this problem to be a subject
of attentive exploration. Under his leadership the Department
of Geopolitics and National Security have been preparing systematic
analysis of scientific research in this field and corresponding
questions of defending personal rights and national security.

<OL>
<LI>Conclusion
</OL>

<P>
The English proverb says: &quot;The difference between man and
boy is the cost of their toy&quot;. The modern toys have a monstrous
potential, which can easily turns in destructive power in hands
of modern adult boys. The whole world can become for them such
a toy.
<P>
The phenomenon of total information war can become the most dangerous
threat of our civilization on a threshold of third millennium.
There is the task stated before the mankind. Without refusing
from scientific and technological progress we are to subordinate
it to common values of humanism: &quot;Everyone is free within
the limits of rights of others on the same freedom.&quot;
</td>

